Le 3 avr. 08 =E0 17:24, David Allsopp a =E9crit :

> OT: May I politely suggest that perhaps your coding standards could =20=

> do with
> updating to mitigate part of this. Unless you're still on an 80x25 =20
> character
> terminal limiting yourself to 79 characters per line is pretty =20
> archaic. We
> use 150 character max line limit (and print in landscape if necessary)

Limiting oneself to 80 character per line is not an archaism. It has =20
to do with typographic rules which were designed to cope with how our =20=

vision works, you'll find this in any book about typesetting. Going =20
beyond ~80 characters, it becomes hard to quickly jump from one line =20
to the other when you read (you need to use your thumb).

